  "prompt": "In no more than 200 words please describe a time you gave remarkable service to one of your customer?",
  "response": "During my time at a retail store, a customer came in looking for a specific dress for an upcoming wedding. Unfortunately, we had just sold the last size in her preferred color. Sensing her disappointment, I took the initiative to check our inventory system and discovered that the dress was available at a nearby store. \n\nI offered to call that location, and after securing the dress for her, I arranged for her to pick it up within a few hours. To enhance her experience further, I also provided her with a discount for her next purchase as an apology for the inconvenience.\n\nWhen she returned to thank me, I noticed her face light up with joy upon receiving the dress. She shared how much it meant to her to find the perfect outfit for her special occasion. The positive feedback she gave, along with her return visit to the store, reinforced the impact of personalized service. It was a gratifying moment, showcasing how a little extra effort can transform a customer's experience and foster lasting relationships.",
